author: Kwanwoo Jun
title: North Korea Fires Ballistic Missile Off East Coast, South Korea Says
text:
SEOUL—North Korea fired a ballistic missile off its east coast Sunday morning, South Korea’s Joint Chiefs of Staff said, marking Pyongyang’s first provocation since U.S. President Donald Trump took office last month.

The ballistic missile was launched from Banghyon, in the country’s northwest and just north of Pyongyang, at 7:55 a.m. Seoul time on Sunday, the Joint Chiefs said, as Mr. Trump was hosting Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo...
